We recommended that the Management:
Thru the Inventory Committee, conduct physical inventory of all items of PPE of the LGU, whether acquired through purchase or donation, including those constructed by administration and found at station, taking into consideration the capitalization threshold of P50,000.00, in accordance with the procedures prescribed in COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
Update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile the same with accounting records to make the records reflective of the actual count of PPEs;
Instruct the GSO to cancel the Property Acknowledgement Receipts of the properties below the capitalization threshold and issue Inventory Custodian Slips in lieu thereof;
Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 
No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and
Direct the GSO to prepare, maintain and update Property Cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to Section 114, Paragraph 4 of the MNGAs for LGUs, Volume I.

We have recommended that the Municipal Accountant undertake the following:

A.	Draw the necessary journal entries to correct the balances of the Donations and Construction in Progress account;

B.	Recognize in the books of accounts of the Municipality the specific Property, Plant and Equipment accounts prior to disposal/turn over/transfer to other government agencies;

C.	Comply with COA Circular No. 92-386 dated October 20, 1992 on the disposal of government properties and ensure that donation/transfer of properties to other government agencies are duly supported with relevant documents prior to its dropping from the books of the Municipality.

We have recommended that the Management, thru the Municipal Mayor, undertake the following courses of action:

Ensure that all properties of the government leased to private individuals/corporations have proper authority from the Sangguniang Bayan and lease transactions are covered with valid contracts;

Collect the additional rental fee including penalties from the Lessee of the Restaurant amounting to P785,000.00 and the additional rental fee including penalties from the Lessee of the Variety Store amounting to P15,000.00 arising from error in computation due to non-compliance to the provisions of Tax Ordinance No. 04, s.2021, otherwise, a Notice of Charge will be issued;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to ensure timely collection of monthly rental fees, otherwise, penalties should be imposed and collected for late payments;

Include in the Contract with the Lessee terms on security deposit/guarantee to insure the government from losses;

Determine the amount of electric and water consumptions of the Variety Store from August 2020 to December 2022, Restaurant from August 2022 to December 2022 and Two-Storey Building for CY 2022 and collect the same from the Lessees, otherwise, a Notice of Disallowance will be issued for the electric and water expenses at the GRHR, which were paid by the LGU; and

Ensure that electric, water and other applicable charges will be collected from the Lessees.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Concerned BAC officials to submit their written explanations/justifications as to why the said transaction should not be disallowed in audit in view of the noted deficiencies in the bidding process;

BAC to ensure the completeness of the PBD prior to its advertisement and posting;

BAC to observe due diligence in the conduct of eligibility checking and post-qualification of the winning bidder to ensure that the contract will only be awarded to suppliers/contractors who are technically eligible; and

BAC to strictly observe the principles of transparency, equity and efficiency in their proceedings in order to prevent sanctions provided under Section 65 of the RA 9184.  
Further, we have recommended that the Municipal Agriculture Officer submit a database or any relevant document, which would provide information on the preferences and planting experience of corn farmers in the Municipality.

