We have recommended that the Management, thru the Local Chief Executive:

Exhaust all possible efforts, including legal remedies, for the immediate settlement of all the unremitted collections of the revenue collectors, including the proper accounting of the 191 pieces of missing/unaccounted AFs. Otherwise, appropriate charges may be imposed for failure to render accounts;

Initiate the filing of appropriate charges against the defaulting accountable/responsible persons;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to exercise the diligence of a good father of a family in supervising the accountable officers under her control, as well as Accountable Forms and reports, to prevent the incurrence of loss of government funds and property pursuant to Sections 69, 104 and 105 of P.D. 1445 and Item B of Section 60 of the Local Treasury Operations Manual to avoid becoming jointly and severally liable with the erring collectors and collecting clerks designated as collectors.

