We recommended that Management:

a.	Create the Inventory Committee composed of adequate number of members to conduct physical inventory of all PPEs of the Municipality within the period prescribed under the aforementioned COA Circular;

b.	Thru the Inventory Committee created, update the property records based on the results of physical inventory, and reconcile with accounting records;

c.	Undertake all other procedures prescribed under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with the reconciled and correct balances of PPE accounts in the financial statements; and 

d.	After the inventory taking, direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare the updated ledger cards for each item of the PPE pursuant to the Section 269 of the GAM for LGUs.

We highly recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the concerned accountable officer to restitute immediately the full amount of missing fund and exhaust all possible efforts to ensure that the said fund will be returned to the coffers of the government. 

Further, we recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Treasurer to update her current accountabilities by ensuring that all collections are deposited in full and up to date and submit a certification from the Accounting Section with regard to that matter;

Likewise, we recommended that management strengthen its internal rules and regulations over its cash management to ensure that it is adequate and effectively implemented.

