We recommended that management strictly comply with the guidelines embodied in the COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015 by ensuring the following:

•	General Service Officer maintains and updates a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all road and its component;

•	Municipal Engineer provides the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components of road projects;


•	Municipal Accountant ensures compliance with the transitory provisions of the Circular by updating the records of the Road Network account, keeps and maintains subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and makes the required disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statement.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Require all accountable officers and employees of the LGU with outstanding balances to immediately settle their accounts giving more emphasis to long outstanding receivables by issuing Demand Letters.
Resort to the withholding of salaries of those accountable officers and employees who still fail or persistently refuse to settle their accounts;
Issue demand letters and exert best efforts for the immediate settlement or recovery of the long outstanding “Other Receivables” from former officers and employees who are no longer in the service nor connected with the LGU;
Observe strictly the proper issuance and release of Clearance from Money and Property accountability from all personnel who seek retirement, resignation, transfer or claim for death benefits to ensure that all accountabilities will be appropriately settled;
Strengthen the internal control system of the LGU with regards to receivables and the corresponding collection in order to safeguard the fund of the government.

